Whether self-taught or Instructor-led, a basic Bioinformatics training should at least be composed of the  following topics:

Slack, Git, and GitHub
UNIX command-line
Shell scripting-A shell script is a computer program designed to be run by a Unix shell,(a text file that contains a sequence of commands for a UNIX-based operating system)It is called a shell script because it combines a sequence of commands, that would otherwise have to be typed into the keyboard one at a time, into a single script. 
Conda
Genome assembly
Strain typing
Database querying
Phylogenetic analysis
Python and machine learning for bioinformatics
Nextflow and Docker
R programming-for Visualization
